    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-10-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-10-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="601" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d601">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-10-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 22,
                                1895</hi>
                        </date>. (Received Nov. 7.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 650.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inclose copy of my
                            note sent last night to the minister of foreign affairs requesting
                            prompt orders for the security of three American missionary ladies at
                            Adabazar. I learned yesterday of their danger on account of a
                            disturbance among the Moslems at Hendek, which is near Adabazar.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">A. W. Terrell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure in No. 650.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to
                                        <persName type="to">Said Pasha</persName>.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">United States Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-10-21">
                                <hi rend="italic">October 21, 1895</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 90.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform your
                                excellency that I learn from a reliable source that a disturbance
                                has taken place at Hendek, in the district of Adabazar. As there are
                                three American ladies residing in the town of Adabazar, in the same
                                district, I request that your excellency will send telegraphic
                                orders at once to the competent authorities in order to insure the
                                safety of these ladies.</p>
                    <p>Receive, etc.,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">A. W. Terrell.</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
        </body>
